---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="Getting Started - Helpmaton">
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen p-8 py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-12 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-display-2 font-display text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">
          Getting Started
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--text-muted)]">
          Start here to set up your first agent
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">1</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Create Your Account
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            First, sign up for Helpmaton. The free plan includes 7-day access, or
            you can try a paid plan. No credit card required.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Click the "Start Free Trial" button on the homepage</li>
            <li>Enter your email address</li>
            <li>Verify your email (check your spam folder)</li>
            <li>You're in! Welcome to Helpmaton</li>
          </ol>
          <div class="mt-4">
            <a
              href="https://app.helpmaton.com"
              class="inline-block bg-neon-cyan text-surface px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg border border-neon-cyan/50 hover:shadow-neon-cyan transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Sign Up Now →
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">2</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Create Your First Workspace
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Workspaces are separate spaces for your agents. Each workspace has
            its own settings, credits, and team members.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>After logging in, click "Create Workspace"</li>
            <li>Give it a name</li>
            <li>
              Set spending limits for AI usage (optional, but recommended)
            </li>
            <li>Invite team members if needed (optional)</li>
            <li>Click "Create" to finish</li>
          </ol>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
              Important: AI Provider Setup
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-2">
              To use AI agents, you'll need to cover AI provider costs (OpenAI,
              Anthropic, Google, etc.). These are <strong
                >separate from your Helpmaton subscription</strong
              >. You have two options:
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4 mb-2"
            >
              <li>
                <strong>Use your own API keys:</strong> Pay providers directly while
                using all Helpmaton features
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Purchase credits:</strong> Buy credits through Helpmaton for
                pay-as-you-go billing
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-2">
              Your subscription covers the platform; AI provider calls are
              billed separately. Set spending limits to stay on budget.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">3</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Create Your First Agent
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Now for the fun part—creating your first agent.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Navigate to your workspace</li>
            <li>Click "Create Agent"</li>
            <li>Give your agent a name and instructions</li>
            <li>Choose what your agent can do</li>
            <li>Add any starting notes or prompts</li>
            <li>Click "Create" to finish</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Pro tip: Start simple. You can add more later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">4</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Upload Documents
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Give your agents knowledge by uploading documents. They'll use what
            you provide to help you faster.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to the "Documents" section in your workspace</li>
            <li>Click "Upload Document"</li>
            <li>Select a Markdown or text file</li>
            <li>Organize documents into folders if needed</li>
            <li>Your agents can now use this knowledge</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Supported formats: Markdown (MD) and plain text.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">5</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Test Your Agent
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Time to see your agent in action. Test it to make sure it works the
            way you expect.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to your agent's page</li>
            <li>Use the test interface to send a message</li>
            <li>Watch your agent respond</li>
            <li>Adjust settings if needed</li>
            <li>Repeat until you're satisfied</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">6</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Connect to Other Apps (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Connect your agent to other apps and services so it can send and
            receive messages. Get fast responses as it works.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create Connection" or set up real-time updates</li>
            <li>Enter your app details</li>
            <li>Configure which events should trigger the connection</li>
            <li>Test it out</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can add app connections later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">7</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Connect External Tools (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Power up your agents by connecting them to external tools and
            services. This lets them access APIs, query databases, and run
            custom actions.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create External Connection"</li>
            <li>Enter the service URL and set up authentication</li>
            <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
            <li>Your agents can now use external tools</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This is an advanced feature, perfect for deeper integrations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">8</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Connect Google Workspace Services (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Connect Gmail, Google Calendar, and Google Drive in a few clicks. No
            complex setup needed. Your agents can manage your calendar, read and
            search emails, and access Drive files.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create MCP Server" or find Google Workspace options</li>
            <li>
              Choose the service you want to connect (Gmail, Google Calendar, or
              Google Drive)
            </li>
            <li>
              Click "Connect Google Account" and sign in with your Google
              account
            </li>
            <li>Grant the necessary permissions</li>
            <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
            <li>Your agents can now access your Google Workspace services!</li>
          </ol>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
              What Your Agents Can Do
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
            >
              <li>
                <strong>Gmail:</strong> Search, read, and manage emails
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Google Calendar:</strong> List events, create meetings, and
                update schedules
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Google Drive:</strong> Read files, Docs, Sheets, and Slides
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-2">
              All connections use secure sign-in to keep your data private.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can connect Google services later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">9</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Connect Notion (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Connect Notion in a few clicks. Your agents can read and search
            pages, create and update content, and work with databases.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>Click "Create MCP Server" and select "Notion"</li>
            <li>
              Click "Connect Notion Account" and sign in with your Notion
              account
            </li>
            <li>Grant the necessary permissions</li>
            <li>Enable the connection for your agents</li>
            <li>Your agents can now access your Notion workspace!</li>
          </ol>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
              What Your Agents Can Do
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
            >
              <li>
                <strong>Read Pages:</strong> Read pages with their content and properties
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Search:</strong> Search pages and databases across your Notion
                workspace
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Create Pages:</strong> Create new pages with content and properties
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Update Pages:</strong> Update page content and properties
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Query Databases:</strong> Filter and sort database entries
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Manage Database Pages:</strong> Create and update database
                entries
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Append Content:</strong> Add blocks like paragraphs, headings,
                and lists
              </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-2">
              All connections use secure sign-in to keep your data private.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can connect Notion later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">10</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Enable Web Search & Content Extraction (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Give your agents access to up-to-date information. Enable web search
            to find current articles and use content extraction to summarize any
            web page.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to your agent's configuration page</li>
            <li>Find the "Web Search" and "Content Extraction" toggles</li>
            <li>
              Enable the features you want (web search, content extraction, or
              both)
            </li>
            <li>Your agents can now use these features</li>
          </ol>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
              Web Search Pricing
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-2">
              All plans include <strong
                >10 free web searches per 24 hours</strong
              >. Additional searches cost <strong>$0.008 each</strong>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mt-2">
              Great for research and monitoring when you need current
              information.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can enable web search later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">11</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Explore Memory & Analytics (Automatic)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Your agents automatically use helpful features built into Helpmaton.
            No setup needed.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>
              <strong>Agent Memory:</strong> Agents remember facts, people, and events
              and organize them over time to provide better answers
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Usage Analytics:</strong> Track usage with daily and hourly
              summaries
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Error Tracking:</strong> Errors show up in conversations when
              requests fail
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Cost Control:</strong> Set spending limits at workspace and
              agent levels to maintain budget control
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            These features work automatically based on your plan.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">12</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Configure Notification Channels (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Set up notification channels so agents can send updates to Discord
            or Slack.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Notification Channels" in your workspace settings</li>
            <li>For Discord: Add a bot token and channel ID</li>
            <li>For Slack: Configure Slack connections in Integrations</li>
            <li>Agents can now send notifications</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can set up notifications later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">13</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Set Up Email Connections (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Set up email access so agents can send emails from your workspace.
          </p>
          <ol
            class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
          >
            <li>Go to "Email Settings" in your workspace</li>
            <li>Configure email authentication</li>
            <li>Verify your email connection</li>
            <li>Agents can now send emails</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can set up email later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/20 bg-surface-100/80 backdrop-blur-sm"
        >
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-2xl font-semibold text-neon-cyan">14</span>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)]">
              Deploy as Slack or Discord Bots (Optional)
            </h2>
          </div>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Deploy your agents as Slack or Discord bots so people can chat with
            them directly.
          </p>
          <div class="mb-4 space-y-4">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Slack Integration
              </h3>
              <ol
                class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
              >
                <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace</li>
                <li>Click "Create Slack Integration"</li>
                <li>Follow the step-by-step guide</li>
                <li>Complete the verification steps</li>
                <li>Your agent can now respond in Slack</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
                Discord Integration
              </h3>
              <ol
                class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
              >
                <li>Go to "Integrations" in your workspace</li>
                <li>Click "Create Discord Integration"</li>
                <li>Follow the step-by-step guide</li>
                <li>Complete verification steps</li>
                <li>Your agent can now respond with slash commands</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="mt-4 p-4 bg-neon-cyan/10 border border-neon-cyan/20 rounded-lg"
          >
            <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">
              Key Features
            </p>
            <ul
              class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] ml-4"
            >
              <li>
                <strong>Unified Management:</strong> Manage integrations from one
                page
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Secure by Default:</strong> Verification keeps requests safe
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Fast Updates:</strong> Responses update as the agent works
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Full Agent Capabilities:</strong> Bots can use the agent’s
                tools and memory
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            This step is optional. You can deploy bots later.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-neon-cyan/20 to-neon-magenta/20 rounded-xl p-6 border border-neon-cyan/30 shadow-neon-cyan text-[var(--text-primary)]"
        >
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">You're All Set!</h2>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Congrats! You've created your first workspace and agent and uploaded
            documents. You're ready to go.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-4 text-[var(--text-muted)]">
            Want to learn more? Explore the docs or join our community.
          </p>
          <div class="flex gap-4 flex-wrap">
            <a
              href="/documentation"
              class="inline-block bg-neon-cyan text-surface px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg border border-neon-cyan/50 hover:shadow-neon-cyan transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Full Documentation
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://app.helpmaton.com/docs/api"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-block border-2 border-neon-cyan/70 bg-transparent text-neon-cyan px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-neon-cyan hover:text-surface transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              API Reference
            </a>
            <a
              href="https://discord.gg/Zf9Q7GpuKx"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="inline-block border-2 border-neon-cyan/70 bg-transparent text-neon-cyan px-4 py-2 font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-neon-cyan hover:text-surface transition-colors text-sm"
            >
              Join Discord
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
